<p>WalkerCMS is a file-driven content-management system (CMS). No database required.</p>
<h2>No DB?</h2>
<p>That's right. No database required.</p>
<p>WalkerCMS is great for small websites that have a few pages of content and where the content
updates are few and far between. The primary motivation has been to provide local small businesses
with a simple web presence.</p>
<h2>Why a CMS then?</h2>
<p>Call me ambitiously lazy. Or, for a more positive spin, I
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don't_repeat_yourself" title="DRY principle">don't like 
to repeat</a> myself. I saw that I was writing the same boilerplate code around content that only
changed based on the link that was clicked. I realized that if the business owners wanted a change
to the look and feel, I would have to make the change on every page.</p>